parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body and Engine Performance Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden loss of power, stalling, and safety risks while driving.

The failure of the Fuel Pump Electronic Module can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to dangerous situations, especially when driving on hills or in traffic. This can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or has difficulty starting
the engine takes time to turn over
the gas pedal is slow to respond to acceleration
the check engine light is on
and fuel fumes are present around the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: the check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle is unable to restart immediately.

the check engine warning light illuminates
